devdoc.details: A smart-contract based mechanism to distribute tokens over time, based on implementation of ampleforth's TokenGeyser contract (see: [token-geyser]).  /// Token that users stake is any ERC20 token defined on contract deployment. Users are rewarded in distribution tokens, which in this case will be KEEP.  /// Account holding Reward Distribution role locks tokens for distribution. The role can be transferred to any account or contract (e.g. Escrow) by the contract owner.  /// [token-geyser]: https://github.com/ampleforth/token-geyser/

params._bonusPeriodSec: Length of time for bonus to increase linearly to max.
params._distributionToken: The token users are rewarded in and receive it as they unstake.
params._durationSec: Length of time to linear unlock the rewards tokens.
params._initialSharesPerToken: Number of shares to mint per staking token on first stake.
params._maxUnlockSchedules: Max number of unlock stages, to guard against hitting gas limit.
params._stakingToken: The token users deposit as a stake.
params._startBonus: Starting time bonus, BONUS_DECIMALS fixed point. e.g. 25% means user gets 25% of max distribution tokens.

getDistributionToken().return: The token users receive as they unstake.

getStakingToken().return: The token users deposit as stake.

isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

params.amount: Number of distribution tokens to lock. These are transferred from the caller.
params.durationSec: Length of time to linear unlock the tokens.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._from: The owner of the tokens who approved them to stake.
params._value: Approved amount of tokens for the transfer.
